UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393286900760
AB  - A rational expectations model is presented to generalize McCallum and Whitaker's (1979) model. The model demonstrates the effectiveness and stability of the full-employment budget deficit and of inflationary finance used to finance this deficit as automatic stabilizers in the determination of current income under rational expectations. Within the same model the problem of optimal dynamic stochastic monetary policy is also briefly explored.
